Subject: [PATCH 1882/2288] Binius QueryPhase: land StateT.run-evaluated forIn
 support bridge; sharpen toFun_full residual
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The `toFun_full` reduction collapses the verifier run to membership in the support of
`StateT.run (OptionT (StateT σ ProbComp)-loop) s`.  Analysing that support needs an invariant
rule for the loop, but `ForInSupport.forIn_support_invariant` requires `[HasEvalSet m]` for the
loop monad and `HasEvalSet (StateT σ ProbComp)` does NOT exist — `support` only lives at the
`ProbComp` level reached after `StateT.run … s`.  The prior residual claimed this machinery was
"in hand"; it was not.

This commit supplies the genuinely missing primitive, proven honestly (axioms ⊆
[propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound]; no sorryAx / native_decide / new axioms):

  * `ForInSupport.stateT_run_forIn_cons_mem` — cons-step support membership for the
    `StateT.run … s`-evaluation of an `OptionT (StateT σ ProbComp)` `forIn`, via
    `List.forIn_cons` + the monad-instance unfolds (landing at a `ProbComp`-level bind) +
    `mem_support_bind_iff`.
  * `ForInSupport.stateT_run_forIn_support_invariant` — the induction-free `Inv`-rule (the
    `OptionT (StateT σ ProbComp)` analogue of `forIn_support_invariant`), usable on the
    `simulateQ`-collapsed verifier run.

In `toFun_full`, lands the verified outer-map peel (`map_eq_pure_bind`: the map is the OptionT
functor map, NOT a StateT map — `StateT.run_map` does not fire) and rewrites the residual to
rest on the real primitive above: (1) outer no-early-exit via the new invariant with
`Inv acc := acc.fst = none`, (2) per-rep inner invariant, (3) the unchanged BaseFold cast
alignment (the genuine remaining content).  The rbrKnowledgeSoundness residual is corrected to
cite the new bridge rather than the inapplicable `forIn_support_invariant`.

