 (ArkLib#3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Migrate the four sanctioned `OracleVerifier.liftContext`/`OracleReduction.liftContext`
call sites broken by the new oracle-routing lens API (commit acd9ca84):

- Build `sumcheckOracleLens`, the concrete `OracleStatement.OracleLens` for the
  single-round sum-check virtual reduction. `toLens` reuses the existing value-level
  `oStmtLens` verbatim; `simOStmt` answers each inner univariate evaluation query at
  `pt` by the `|D|^(n-1)`-fold summation of the outer multivariate oracle over the
  real `Fin.insertNth` evaluation point (`sumPoint`), reading prior challenges from the
  outer statement via `ReaderT`; `embedOStmt`/`hEqOStmt` draw the single output oracle
  from the unchanged input oracle.
- `oracleVerifier` / `oracleReduction` now pass `sumcheckOracleLens` to the
  re-signatured `liftContext`.
- The lifted `oracleReduction_perfectCompleteness` and
  `oracleVerifier_rbrKnowledgeSoundness` thread the new `LiftContextCoherent` side
  condition (`toVerifier_comm`) as a hypothesis, exactly as the upstream
  `liftContext_perfectCompleteness` / `liftContext_rbr_knowledgeSoundness` now do.
  `hStmt := rfl` since `sumcheckOracleLens.toLens` and `(oCtxLens …).stmt` are both
  `oStmtLens …`.

Zero new sorries (the 7 remaining are the pre-existing Simpler-namespace component
sorries). File compiles green.

