MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add the reusable failure-monotone probabilistic core of rbrSoundness → soundness:

- probEvent_bind_trailing_le (RoundByRound): appending a possibly-failing
  computation before returning a prefix-only value can only decrease event
  probability (the marginal relation is ≤, not =).
- probEvent_simulateQ_run'_bind_trailing_le (RoundByRound): the STATE-AWARE
  transport of the above across simulateQ over an ARBITRARY stateful
  QueryImpl (StateT σ ProbComp), threaded through .run' — the connective that
  lets the full run's trailing receiveChallenge/sendMessage/output/verifier
  steps be dropped while keeping the impl/state thread both games share.
- fin_take_snoc_of_le (Execution): geometric prefix-preservation under snoc.

Also: corrected a FALSE-equality trap — the prover-prefix marginal CANNOT be a
plain computation equality (sendMessage/receiveChallenge return failing
OracleComp), only a failure-monotone ≤; recorded precise FRONTIER NOTE in
Execution.lean and proof spine in Implications.lean.

No new sorries beyond the two named targets + pre-existing L… one-shot lemma.

